Natural Key
A natural key is a column that comes from real-world data and already exists.
It has meaning in the business.

Example: email, SSN, passport number
It is easy to understand, but it can change and may not always be reliable.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Surrogate Key
A surrogate key is a system-generated value used to identify each row.
It has no real-world meaning.
Example: auto-increment ID
It is simple, always unique, and does not change.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Difference

A natural key comes from real data and has meaning.
A surrogate key is created by the system and has no meaning.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Natural keys can change.
Surrogate keys do not change.

----------------------------------------------------
